55 publication, that routinely carries news and commentary of general interest, and that publishes a
56 materially deceptive election-related communication prohibited by this section, if the publication
57 clearly states that such communication is manipulated or that there are questions about its
58 authenticity.
59 (5) This section shall not apply to materially deceptive election-related communications
60 that constitute satire or parody.
